cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with channel decoding, which is a topic related to information theory and communication systems. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the uncertainty in the channel state information (CSI) estimate, which is a topic related to networked systems and control theory, making cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper proposes a Bayesian equalizer, which is a statistical method, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category.
